      <h1>About</h1>
      <p class="intro">
        Chris Randall is a composer, recording artist, and music technology entrepreneur based in Bellows Falls, Vermont. Born in Honolulu in 1968 and raised between New York City and rural Oregon, he began his career in Chicago's legendary Wax Trax! Records mailroom before rising to front the industrial rock band Sister Machine Gun, releasing eight studio albums between 1992 and 2015. His music has been placed in numerous film and television productions, including Scream, Hideaway, La Femme Nikita, Dateline NBC, and over two decades of MTV programming.
      </p>
      <p class="intro">
        Beyond Sister Machine Gun, Randall has released a prolific catalog of electronic and experimental music under the Micronaut moniker and his own name. In 1998, he founded the now-defunct Positron! Records, and in 2002 co-founded <a href="https://www.audiodamage.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Audio Damage, Inc.</a>, a software and hardware synthesizer company whose products are used by artists and composers worldwide. His work spans industrial rock, IDM, ambient, and cinematic composition, bringing a unique production sensibility shaped by decades of studio experience and electronic music innovation.
      </p>
